    slug: "kids-story-books-set-qasas-ul-anbiya-set-of-30-books",
    description: `Kids Story Books Set - Qasas ul Anbiya is a complete collection of thirty individual storybooks that narrate the lives and missions of the prophets of Allah in a format specially designed for young readers. Each book in this comprehensive set is dedicated to one or more prophets, presenting their stories in simple, engaging Urdu prose that children can easily understand and enjoy. The series follows the Quranic and authentic hadith accounts of each prophet's life, ensuring that the content is religiously accurate while being presented in an age-appropriate manner that captures the imagination of young minds. From the story of Prophet Adam (peace be upon him) and the beginning of human creation, through the narratives of Prophet Nuh and the great flood, Prophet Ibrahim and his unwavering faith, Prophet Musa and his confrontation with Pharaoh, Prophet Isa and his miraculous birth, to the final messenger Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) and the establishment of Islam, each story is told with vivid descriptions and clear moral lessons that children can absorb and apply in their own lives. The books are designed with child-friendly layouts featuring clear typography, illustrations where appropriate, and short chapters that maintain the child's attention throughout. Each storybook highlights the key lessons from the prophet's life, such as the importance of patience in adversity, the power of sincere prayer, the consequences of arrogance and disobedience, the value of honesty and trustworthiness, and the ultimate victory of truth over falsehood. The thirty-book structure allows parents and teachers to introduce the stories gradually, reading one book at a time and discussing its lessons before moving on to the next. This approach makes the series ideal for use in Islamic schools, madrasahs, and home education settings, as well as for bedtime reading that instils Islamic values in children from a young age. The complete set provides a thorough introduction to all the major prophets mentioned in the Quran, giving children a comprehensive understanding of Islamic history and the continuous chain of divine guidance that culminated in the message of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him).`,
