    slug: "kindness-to-parents",
    description: `Kindness to Parents is a profoundly important Islamic book that thoroughly examines one of the most emphasised obligations in Islam: the duty of children to treat their parents with honour, respect, and unwavering kindness. The book systematically presents the extensive evidence from the Quran and the authentic Sunnah that establishes the supreme status of parental rights in Islam, demonstrating that this obligation ranks alongside the most fundamental acts of worship. The author opens with a detailed analysis of the Quranic verses that address the rights of parents, most notably the commandment in Surah Al-Isra that joins the worship of Allah alone with the requirement to be kind to parents, indicating the immense significance Islam places on this duty. The book explores the various dimensions of parental kindness that Islam prescribes, including obedience to parents within the bounds of Shariah, speaking to them with respect and gentle words, caring for them in their old age, providing for their needs, praying for their forgiveness, and honouring their friends even after they have passed away. The hadith narrations of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) on this topic are presented comprehensively, including his statement that the pleasure of Allah lies in the pleasure of the parents and His displeasure lies in their displeasure. The book also addresses practical aspects of fulfilling this obligation in contemporary life, such as balancing respect for parents with marital responsibilities, managing situations where parents make unreasonable demands, dealing with non-Muslim parents, and maintaining good relations with parents after marriage. The author discusses the common mistakes and shortcomings that children make in their treatment of parents, providing corrective advice based on Islamic teachings. A dedicated section covers the rights of mothers specifically, given the Quranic emphasis on the mother's sacrifices during pregnancy, childbirth, and nursing. The book also addresses the spiritual consequences of being kind to parents, including the promise of increased lifespan, expanded provision, and entry into paradise. Written in clear and accessible language, this book is essential reading for every Muslim who wishes to understand and fulfil one of their most significant religious obligations, as well as for educators and counsellors who guide families on matters of Islamic conduct.`,
    metaDescription: "Kindness to Parents explores Quranic and hadith teachings on honouring parents, covering obedience, care, spiritual rewards, and practical guidance."
