    slug: "kitab-al-azkaar",
    description: `Kitab Al-Azkaar is a comprehensive and authoritative Urdu-language compilation of supplications (azkaar and adhkar) drawn from the authentic Quranic verses and verified hadith narrations of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him). This book serves as an essential daily companion for Muslims who wish to structure their day around the remembrance of Allah, providing a complete collection of the prophetic supplications for every conceivable occasion and situation. The content is meticulously organised to follow the natural progression of a Muslim's daily routine, beginning with the azkaar for waking up in the morning and proceeding through supplications for entering and leaving the mosque, before and after the five daily prayers, for eating and drinking, for wearing new clothes, for travelling, for sleeping, and for every other significant moment in a person's day. Each supplication is presented in its original Arabic text alongside its Urdu translation and transliteration, making it accessible to readers with varying levels of Arabic proficiency. The compiler has paid special attention to verifying the authenticity of each narration, clearly indicating the source and strength of every hadith, which distinguishes this book from less rigorous collections that may include weak or fabricated supplications. The book also includes sections on the supplications for specific needs and circumstances, such as azkaar for seeking forgiveness (istighfar), for expressing gratitude (shukr), for protection from evil, for healing during illness, for ease during times of hardship, and for the deceased. A particularly valuable section covers the morning and evening azkaar (azkaar as-sabah wa al-masa), which the Prophet strongly recommended for every Muslim as a means of spiritual protection and blessings throughout the day. The compiler has also included the supplications from the Quran, particularly those found in the concluding verses of Surah Al-Baqarah and the various prophetic prayers recorded in the authentic hadith collections. The book is designed for practical daily use, with a clear layout, comprehensive indexing, and a durable binding that withstands frequent handling. This compilation is indispensable for every Muslim household, serving as a constant reminder of the importance of maintaining a living connection with Allah through regular supplication and remembrance.`,
    metaDescription: "Kitab Al-Azkaar is a verified Urdu compilation of daily prophetic supplications covering morning, evening, prayer, travel, and every life occasion."
