    slug: "kitab-al-janaiz-mout-se-soug-tak-ke-tamam-masail-ka-encyclopedia",
    description: `Kitab Al-Janaiz (Mout Se Soug Tak Ke Tamam Masail Ka Encyclopedia) is an encyclopaedic Urdu-language reference work that provides exhaustive coverage of every Islamic ruling and procedure related to death, funeral rites, and mourning, from the moment a person's soul departs through the entire mourning period. As its subtitle indicates, this book serves as a complete encyclopaedia of all the issues (masail) that arise between death (mout) and the conclusion of the mourning period (soug), making it one of the most thorough and comprehensive works available on this critically important topic in Islamic jurisprudence. The book begins with the Islamic perspective on death and the dying process, covering the rulings related to a person on their deathbed, including the recommendation to prompt them to recite the shahadah, the etiquette of sitting with the dying person, and the supplications that should be made at this solemn moment. It then proceeds to detail the step-by-step procedure that must be followed after death has been confirmed, including the proper method of closing the eyes and mouth, covering the body, notifying relatives, and preparing for the funeral. The section on ghusl (ritual washing of the deceased) is particularly detailed, covering the requirements, conditions, method, and supplications for washing, as well as the special rulings that apply in different circumstances such as miscarriage, stillbirth, and the washing of martyrs. The chapter on kafan (shrouding) provides precise guidance on the type, quality, and manner of wrapping the deceased according to the Sunnah, with separate instructions for men and women. The funeral prayer (salat al-janazah) is covered comprehensively, including its conditions, pillars, obligations, recommended acts, and the supplications recited during the prayer. The book also addresses burial procedures, the rulings related to the graveyard, and the Islamic etiquette of visiting graves. The section on mourning (soug) covers the specific rulings for the family of the deceased, including the mourning period for widows, the permissibility and prohibition of various mourning practices, and the supplications for the deceased. Written in scholarly yet accessible Urdu, this encyclopaedia is an essential reference for scholars, funeral service providers, and every Muslim household.`,
    metaDescription: "Kitab Al-Janaiz is a complete Urdu encyclopedia of Islamic funeral rites covering ghusl, kafan, salat al-janazah, burial, and mourning rulings."
